<br>
/join &quot;nameofchannelhere&quot;<br>
<br>
Then everything said in the channel will come up in its own colour in your chat window. <br>
<br>
To say something into a channel:<br>
<br>
1) right click on the top bar of the main chat window. <br>
2) move your mouse down over channels, then chat channels, then the channel you want to speak in. You need to have joined it as above for it to be on your list of chat channels to select. <br>
3) Left click on it<br>
4) You should get a message saying suchandsuch is now the default channel for this window, or words to that effect. <br>
5) Everything you type will now go into that channel. <br>
<br>
Niyx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vormorac>Vormorac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/03 12:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG Chat channels - see you there! </span><hr size=1> Thank you! <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Some like to kill their foes quickly from without. Others enjoy slowly devouring them from within.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/03 9:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/10869.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG Chat channels - see you there! </span><hr size=1> Alternatively, if you don't want everything you type to go into that channel, you can use the /# command where # is the number of the channel which shows up when you do the /join nameofthechannelhere.  This number is based entirely on what order you joined the channel in.  In other words, if you join only one channel, /# will always be /1 as you have joined only one channel.<br>
<br>
example:<br>
<br>
/join market<br>
<br>
/join lfg<br>
<br>
/join twisted<br>
<br>
/join lohfriends:friends<br>
<br>
In this case, market would be /1, lfg would be /2, twisted would be /3, and lohfriends would be /4.  Also, there is a password on lohfriends(we are still trying to remove it--it kind of showed up one day and wouldn't leave).  As shown, to enter the password, all you need to do is put a colon and then type the password.<br>
<br>
